title: Janus’s Profit Slides as Assets Under Management Drop
text:
Janus Capital Group Inc. said its third-quarter earnings fell 51% mostly on higher costs, including a big debt-extinguishment charge, that masked underlying revenue growth.
The asset manager said its complex-wide assets totaled $185 billion as of Sept. 30, compared with $192 billion as of June 30, a decline that included net market depreciation of $11 billion and long-term net outflows of $3.3 billion.
